HEADWORD: Sebiferous
<hw>Se*bif"er*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>sebum</ets> tallow + <ets>-ferous</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Producing vegetable tallow.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>Producing fat; sebaceous;
<as>as, the <ex>sebiferous</ex>, or sebaceous, glands</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sebiparous</ent>⟦br⟧
